parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or slip, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the transmission malfunctions
the vehicle stalls
the transmission slips
the RPMs increase rapidly
the vehicle shudders
the vehicle makes a grinding noise
the transmission shutters when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal randomly stays fully depressed
the clutch pedal requires manual intervention to return to its normal position
the operator is distracted due to the inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive axle can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates
the vehicle loses power
the drive axle becomes disconnected at the transmission end.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Valve Sticking due to Gasoline Quality
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking valve can cause the vehicle to buck or lurch while stopping, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle bucks or lurches while stopping
the vehicle revs up and tries to go forward while stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective canister purge valve can cause the vehicle to hesitate while shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates while shifting gears
the accelerator pedal needs to be depressed multiple times before the vehicle accelerates properly
the vehicle displays electrical shortages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: None, as this complaint is unfounded and lacks any technical basis.
symptoms: None
as this complaint is unrelated to any vehicle malfunction or defect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexplained loss of control can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle seems to lift or rise off the ground and move to the right
the vehicle is involved in an accident with a semi-truck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission clutch shudder can cause the vehicle to vibrate or jerk while driving, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences excessive transmission clutch shudder
error code P087E is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The trunk lid can suddenly open while driving, causing a distraction and potential loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The trunk lid opens randomly while driving or when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vent system actuator can cause a crackling noise, which can be a distraction to the driver, and potentially lead to a loss of control.
symptoms: The vent system makes a crackling noise
and the vent fails to open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water coolant container lines can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing a loss of control.
symptoms: Water coolant leaks from the container lines
causing the engine to overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS, Brake, and TSC System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS, brake, and TSC systems can cause the vehicle to jerk to one side, slow down, and potentially lose control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The ABS
brake
and TSC lights illuminate
and the vehicle jerks to one side
slowing down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body control module can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function properly
occasionally draining the battery
and the brake lights may work intermittently while moving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a complete loss of power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system shuts down completely
resulting in no power
no engine
no lights
and no electrical component function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the broken cable connector can cause a complete loss of power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system shuts down completely
resulting in no power
no engine
no lights
and no electrical component function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates forward at a fast rate
often without warning
and may be accompanied by a shuddering or jerking sensation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to jerk, vibrate, or sputter, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks
vibrates
or sputters
especially when driving uphill
and may cause the seatbelt to be activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage and potential breakdowns.
symptoms: The fan stops working
causing the vehicle to overheat
and may occur multiple times even after replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system failure can lead to failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light indicates that the airbag is off even when a passenger is present
and airbags may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting
and may stay at one RPM
causing the vehicle to jerk or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turn signal failure can increase the risk of accidents by reducing the vehicle's visibility to other drivers.
symptoms: The turn signal fails to work
even after replacement and inspection by multiple mechanics.
